Now, we need to use the definition of the `rnDeriv` of `-μ` with respect to `μ.var`.

The `rnDeriv` of `-μ` with respect to `μ.var` is the function `f` such that for all sets `s`, `(-μ) s = ∫ s, f ∂μ.var`.
Since `(-μ) s = - (μ s)`, we have ` - (μ s) = ∫ s, f ∂μ.var`.
Also, `μ s = ∫ s, (μ.rnDeriv μ.var) ∂μ.var`.
Therefore, ` - (∫ s, (μ.rnDeriv μ.var) ∂μ.var) = ∫ s, f ∂μ.var`.
By the uniqueness of the Radon-Nikodym derivative, `f = - (μ.rnDeriv μ.var)`.

